Rebalance for 50-60min playthrough + scaling difficulty

Pacing:
- Slowed idle time progression from 15 to 5 game-min/sec (~5 min/game-day)
- 3-4x higher XP requirements for late careers (Mogul: 1600 -> 6500 XP)
- Added XP fatigue: repeating the same action key in a day gives diminishing
  returns (XP_FATIGUE=0.8 per repeat, floored at 25%) -- forces variety
- Stricter win condition: must be Hot Dog Mogul AND have $250,000 net worth
- Added live goal tracker to the HUD

Difficulty scales with progression:
- Daily rent inflation (+4% per day, mansion balloons fast)
- Factory upkeep costs ($40 + automation*$60), brokerage fees per share
- Random event probability climbs with day (45% -> 80%)
- Stock volatility grows with day (boom & bust eras)
- Energy/mood drain rates scale with career level (executive burnout)
- Tax day takes higher % the deeper into the game you are
- Late-game-only disasters added (factory fires, PR scandals)
- Sickness now lasts multiple days, drains stats, costs visit to clear

Save format bumped to v3 (old saves won't auto-load).
